SIMPLE: lonely
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lonely
<hw>Lone"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Lonelier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Loneliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[Shortened fr.
<ets>alonely</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sequestered from company or
neighbors; solitary; retired; <as>as, a <ex>lonely</ex> situation; a
<ex>lonely</ex> cell.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Alone, or in want of company; forsaken.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To the misled and <qex>lonely</qex> traveler.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not frequented by human beings; <as>as, a
<ex>lonely</ex> wood</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Having a feeling of depression or sadness resulting
from the consciousness of being alone; lonesome.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am very often alone. I don't mean I am <qex>lonely</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>H. James.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Solitary; lone; lonesome; retired; unfrequented;
sequestered; secluded.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loneness</ent>⟦br⟧
